Pinus canariensis

   [8620.jpg]
    Authority   C. Sm.
      Family    Pinopsida:Pinaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names Canary Islands pine, pinheiro das Canarias
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 8620

   Notes
   DESCRIPTION: It is an evergreen, coniferous tree reaching 20-40 m or
   even up to 60 m in height. Needles densely crowded giving the tree a
   tufted appearance, bark furrowed, reddish brown. USE: Timber used for
   construction purposes. The bark yields resin and the tree is grown for
   shelter. GROWING PERIOD: Relatively slow growing perennial. COMMON
   NAMES: Canary Island Pine, pino Canario. FURTHER INF: It can be found
   at elevations from 400 to 2500 m, most common between 600-2000 m. The
   tree occur naturally within the latitudinal range of 27.5-29Â°N. The
   tree can reach a height of 20-30 m. The tree is drought hardy, fire
   resistant and tolerates salt winds. Annual wood production potential is
   8-18 m3/ha.

   Sources
   SOURCES (22.05.02) E8620
   Webb D 1984 pp 207 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, PH, DRA, DEP, LIG, USE]
   INSPIRE species 124 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, PH, DRA, DEP, LIG, USE]

